<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Standards - ToolCalcs"
  description="How ToolCalcs researches, writes, and maintains accurate financial and educational content. Our editorial process, data sources, and correction policy."
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <h1>Editorial Standards</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">ToolCalcs is committed to providing accurate, unbiased, and up-to-date information. This page explains our editorial process, how we source data, and how we handle corrections.</p>

    <h2>Our Editorial Mission</h2>
    <p>Financial, health, and tax topics fall into what Google and the broader information community call "Your Money or Your Life" (YMYL) categories — areas where inaccurate information can directly harm people's financial well-being, health, or safety. We take this responsibility seriously.</p>
    <p>Our goal is to present information that is:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Accurate:</strong> Sourced from primary, authoritative sources</li>
      <li><strong>Current:</strong> Updated when laws, rates, or regulations change</li>
      <li><strong>Complete:</strong> Covers the topic sufficiently to be genuinely useful</li>
      <li><strong>Transparent:</strong> Shows sources, formulas, and limitations openly</li>
      <li><strong>Balanced:</strong> Presents evidence without promoting particular financial products or services</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Primary Data Sources</h2>
    <p>We use the following primary sources for financial and regulatory data:</p>

    <h3>Tax & Government</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>IRS.gov</strong> — Tax brackets, standard deductions, contribution limits, form instructions</li>
      <li><strong>Social Security Administration (SSA.gov)</strong> — FICA wage bases, benefit calculations</li>
      <li><strong>Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS.gov)</strong> — Salary data, employment statistics, CPI/inflation data</li>
      <li><strong>Department of Labor (DOL.gov)</strong> — 401(k) and retirement plan regulations</li>
      <li><strong>Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB)</strong> — Mortgage regulations, consumer credit rules</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Real Estate & Mortgages</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Freddie Mac Primary Mortgage Market Survey</strong> — Weekly mortgage rate benchmarks</li>
      <li><strong>National Association of Realtors (NAR)</strong> — Home price data, market statistics</li>
      <li><strong>HUD.gov</strong> — FHA loan limits, housing assistance programs</li>
      <li><strong>SBA.gov</strong> — Small Business Administration loan terms and rate guidelines</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Health & Wellness</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>World Health Organization (WHO)</strong> — BMI classification standards</li>
      <li><strong>National Institutes of Health (NIH)</strong> — Dietary guidelines, clinical reference data</li>
      <li><strong>American College of Sports Medicine (ACSM)</strong> — Exercise and metabolic rate research</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Investing & Personal Finance</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Federal Reserve (federalreserve.gov)</strong> — Survey of Consumer Finances (net worth data), interest rate data</li>
      <li><strong>SEC.gov</strong> — Investment regulations, investor education materials</li>
      <li><strong>FINRA</strong> — Brokerage and investment industry standards</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Calculator Formula Standards</h2>
    <p>Every calculator on ToolCalcs uses established, peer-validated formulas:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Loan amortization:</strong> Standard fixed-payment annuity formula: M = P[r(1+r)^n]/[(1+r)^n-1]</li>
      <li><strong>Compound interest:</strong> A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt) — standard compound interest formula</li>
      <li><strong>BMI:</strong> WHO standard formula: weight (kg) / height² (m²)</li>
      <li><strong>TDEE/BMR:</strong> Mifflin-St Jeor equation — the most validated formula for general populations per NIH research</li>
      <li><strong>Tax calculations:</strong> Progressive marginal bracket calculation per IRS published rate schedules</li>
      <li><strong>Mortgage refinance:</strong> Standard break-even calculation: closing costs ÷ monthly savings</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Formulas are displayed on calculator pages where space allows, and cited in the educational content accompanying each tool.</p>

    <h2>Update & Review Cycle</h2>
    <p>We maintain a regular review schedule for time-sensitive content:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Annual (January):</strong> Federal tax brackets, standard deductions, 401(k)/IRA/HSA contribution limits, Social Security wage base, Medicare rates, FICA rates</li>
      <li><strong>Quarterly:</strong> Mortgage rate benchmarks, prime rate (for SBA loan calculations), Social Security benefit adjustments</li>
      <li><strong>On regulatory change:</strong> Any article affected by new legislation, IRS rulings, or regulatory changes is updated within 30 days of the effective date</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Every page displays a "Last updated" date so readers can assess currency.</p>

    <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not accept payment to feature or recommend specific financial products, lenders, or services</li>
      <li>We do not publish affiliate-driven content that promotes products our editorial team has not independently evaluated</li>
      <li>We do not present personal opinions as financial advice</li>
      <li>We do not republish content without attribution to primary sources</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>ToolCalcs content is for <strong>informational and educational purposes only</strong>. It does not constitute financial, tax, legal, investment, or medical advice. Calculators use standardized national averages and formulas — individual results will vary based on local laws, personal circumstances, and factors our tools cannot fully account for.</p>
    <p>For decisions involving significant money, taxes, legal matters, or health, consult a qualified professional: Certified Public Accountant (CPA), Certified Financial Planner (CFP), licensed attorney, or licensed healthcare provider.</p>

    <h2>Corrections Policy</h2>
    <p>We take errors seriously. If you identify an inaccuracy — a wrong figure, outdated regulation, or calculation error — please contact us immediately:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Email: <a href="mailto:contact@toolcalcs.com">contact@toolcalcs.com</a></li>
      <li>Subject line: "Accuracy Issue — [page URL]"</li>
      <li>Include: the specific error, the correct information, and your source</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We investigate all accuracy reports. Confirmed errors are corrected within 5 business days and the page's "Last updated" date is refreshed. Significant corrections include an editor's note on the affected page.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about our editorial process? Reach our team at <a href="mailto:contact@toolcalcs.com">contact@toolcalcs.com</a> or visit our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>
